# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo

# Big artifacts we don't want in git
data/raw/
data/processed/

# BUT keep our bundled serving model in the repo
!src/serving/model/
!src/serving/model/**

#The .gitignore file keeps the repository clean and lightweight
#by preventing unnecessary files—such as virtual environments,
#cache files, large data folders, and experiment artifacts—from being tracked in Git. 
#However, it explicitly allows the serving model folder to be included, ensuring that 
#the required production model is still available in the repository.'''